  "title": "Sustained Neural Representations of Personally Familiar People and Places During Cued Recall",
  "description": "This dataset contains neuroimaging data from a cued recall task investigating sustained neural representations of personally familiar people and places. Participants were cued to recall specific individuals and locations while MEG data were recorded, enabling investigation of how the brain maintains and represents autobiographical memories of social and spatial information.",
